      "span_text": "In this study, we ablated cochlear hair cells in C57Bl/ 6 mice using a combination of subcutaneous kanamycin and intraperitoneal furosemide as described by Oesterle et al. [CITATION_1] We then treated the left ear of each animal by injecting Ad28.gfap.atoh1 vector into the perilymph via a posterior canal injection, leaving the right ear untreated to serve as an internal control.",
